<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  HC career-level statistic.

  Dual-purpose: it both tracks Karrierestufe 0..5 for the Layer A pie-menu
  promotion flow (see historian_career.py TIERS) AND is referenced as
  `performance_stat` on every career_level_Adult_Historian_L*.xml, which drives
  the per-shift performance bar in the expanded Career Panel
  (PerformanceDetails.as in the Olympus UI).

  Field names per EA's `statistics.statistic.Statistic` tunable schema.
  Reference: Mod-Constructor-5 (MIT) — Constructor5.Elements/Statistics/
  Statistic.cs and Constructor5/TuningActions/*.xml. The canonical EA names
  are:
    - min_value_tuning       (Int)        — lower bound
    - max_value_tuning       (Int)        — upper bound
    - initial_tuning         (Tuple)      — starting value:
        ._initial_value      (Int)
        ._use_stat_value_on_init (Bool)
    - persisted_tuning       (Bool)       — saved with the sim

  PREVIOUSLY (caused fix/career-progressbar-range bug; user-reported
  lastUIException.txt 2026-05-13): this file used `min_value` / `max_value` /
  `initial_value` / `stat_type` — none of which exist in EA's Statistic
  schema. The Python tuning loader silently ignored every one of them and
  the stat fell back to class-level defaults that leave min == max == 0.

  When the Career Panel widget called

    mcProgressBar.SetRange(performanceData.min_value,
                           performanceData.max_value)

  with min == max == 0, EA's olympus.gui.progressbars.ProgressBar.SetRange()
  threw

    Error: ProgressBar: Maximum cannot be equal to minimum
        at olympus.gui.progressbars::ProgressBar/SetRange()
        at widgets.Gameplay.SimInfoHUD.CareerPanel::PerformanceDetails/Draw()

  and the panel refused to open after `careers.add_career career_Adult_Historian`.

  The bar's `performanceData.min_value` / `.max_value` come from this stat
  via the `performance_stat` reference on each CareerLevel — every L1..L5
  level of `career_Adult_Historian` points here.

  Range choice: kept 0..5 to preserve the existing Layer A semantics in
  historian_career.TIERS (1->HiWi ... 5->Professor) and the
  HC_Loot_Add_HistorianLevel_* loot actions. The bar saturating quickly at
  +8 per shift / +5 per completed goal is a quality issue, not a crash,
  and is a v0.2 polish item (split into a separate
  per-shift performance Commodity with -100..+100 range, the EA-standard
  shape).

  Dropped from the previous shape (none were valid Statistic tunables):
    - stat_type             (not a class tunable; class identity is `c=`)
    - remove_on_convergence (Commodity-only; Statistic has no convergence)

  Bare Statistic is the right class here: it has no decay/convergence and
  no buff-state machine, both of which a per-tier counter explicitly does
  not want.
-->
<I c="Statistic" i="statistic" m="statistics.statistic" n="HC_Statistic_HistorianLevel" s="TBD_INSTANCE_ID">
  <T n="min_value_tuning">0</T>
  <T n="max_value_tuning">5</T>
  <U n="initial_tuning">
    <T n="_initial_value">0</T>
    <T n="_use_stat_value_on_init">True</T>
  </U>
  <T n="persisted_tuning">True</T>
</I>
